{{wikipedia|Future}}
==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin '''[[futurus]]''', irregular future participle of '''[[esse]]''', ''be''.

===Pronunciation===
* (''[[Received Pronunciation|UK]]'') {{IPA|/ˈfjuːʧə/}}, {{SAMPA|/"fju:tS@/}}
* (''[[General American|US]]'') {{IPA|/ˈfjuːʧɚ/}}, {{SAMPA|/"fju:tS@`/}}
* {{audio|en-us-future.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-uːtʃə(r)|-uːtʃə(r)]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|-}}

# The [[time]] [[ahead]]; those [[moment]]s [[yet]] to be [[experience]]d.
# Something that will happen in moments yet to come.
#: ''There is no future in [[dwelling]] on the [[past]].
# (''grammatical terminology''): verb tense used to talk about events that will happen in the future. [[future tense]]
# {{finance}} ''(plural)'' [[commodities|Commodities]] or [[stocks]] [[bought]] or [[sold]] with the [[understanding]] that they will be delivered at a [[date]] [[beyond]] the [[current]] one.

